doctype html
html
  head
    title Creator Agreement | Eporia
    meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Nunito:wght@400;600;700;800;900&display=swap')
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css")
    link(rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/layout.css')
    style.
      /* Reusing Legal Styles */
      body { background-color: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-main); line-height: 1.8; }
      .legal-container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 60px 20px; }
      .legal-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 60px; }
      .legal-header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .last-updated { opacity: 0.6; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 700; }
      
      .legal-section { margin-bottom: 40px; background: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 20px; box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft); border: 1px solid #eee; }
      .legal-section h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 15px; }
      .legal-section h2 i { color: var(--accent-orange); font-size: 1.2rem; }
      .legal-section p { margin-bottom: 15px; opacity: 0.9; }
      .legal-section ul { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin-bottom: 15px; }
      .legal-section li { margin-bottom: 12px; position: relative; padding-left: 25px; }
      .legal-section li::before { content: "•"; color: var(--primary); font-weight: bold; position: absolute; left: 0; }
      
      .guarantee-box { 
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(136, 201, 161, 0.1) 0%, rgba(136, 201, 161, 0.2) 100%);
        padding: 30px; 
        border-radius: 15px; 
        border: 2px solid var(--primary); 
        margin: 20px 0;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .guarantee-badge { 
        display: inline-block; background: var(--primary); color: white; 
        padding: 5px 15px; border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 800; font-size: 0.8rem; margin-bottom: 15px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px;
      }
      
      /* New Style for Point System */
      .points-table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin-top: 20px;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
      .points-table th { text-align: left; color: var(--text-muted); border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; padding: 10px; }
      .points-table td { padding: 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; }
      .points-highlight { color: var(--accent-orange); font-weight: 800; }

  body
    .legal-container
      .legal-header
        h1 Creator Agreement
        p.last-updated Last Updated: February 2026

      //- 1. APPOINTMENT OF AGENT
      .legal-section
        h2 
          i.fas.fa-handshake
          | 1. Appointment & Revenue Split
        p By using Eporia, you appoint Eporia as your <strong>limited payment collection agent</strong>. We collect subscription fees from fans on your behalf.
        
        h3(style="font-size:1.1rem; margin-top:20px; font-weight:800") The "User-Centric" Model
        p Eporia does not use a "big pot" model where your streams are weighed against the entire world. Instead, every subscriber's fee is treated as a distinct wallet. 
        p <strong>How You Get Paid:</strong>
        ul
            li <strong>Platform Fee:</strong> Eporia retains 20% to 30% of the gross subscription fee (depending on the user's allocation mode) to cover payment processing (Stripe), server costs, and platform development.
            li <strong>Net Allocatable Funds:</strong> The remaining 70% to 80% constitutes the "Creator Share."
            li <strong>Metric-Based Distribution:</strong> This Creator Share is distributed <strong>only</strong> to the artists that the specific subscriber engages with. Engagement is measured via our "Proof of Fandom" metrics—specifically <strong>Follows</strong>, <strong>Likes</strong>, and <strong>Crate Additions</strong>—ensuring money flows to the artists users actually value, not just background noise.
        
        .guarantee-box
          .guarantee-badge No Dilution Guarantee
          h3(style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: 900") Your Fans, Your Money
          p(style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0")
            | If a fan supports you, their money comes to you. Your earnings are derived from the Net Allocatable Funds of your specific listeners and are never diluted to pay for streams on the "Top 40" charts.

      //- 2. ALLOCATION METHODS (NEW)
      .legal-section
        h2 
          i.fas.fa-chart-pie
          | 2. Allocation Methods
        p Subscribers control how their funds are distributed using one of two methods. Your payout depends on which method the subscriber selects.

        h3(style="font-size:1.1rem; margin-top:25px; font-weight:800") A. Manual Allocation (80% Payout)
        p The subscriber explicitly selects you as a beneficiary.
        ul
          li User manually assigns a dollar amount or percentage to your profile.
          li <strong>Payout Rate:</strong> 80% of allocated funds go to you.

        h3(style="font-size:1.1rem; margin-top:25px; font-weight:800") B. Auto-Allocation (70% Payout)
        p The subscriber opts for Eporia's algorithmic distribution. Funds are distributed to artists based on a "Proof of Fandom" engagement score.
        ul
          li <strong>Payout Rate:</strong> 70% of allocated funds go to you.
          li <em>Why the difference?</em> The additional 10% fee covers the computational resources required to verify authentic engagement and prevent bot-driven "stream farming."
        
        p <strong>The "Proof of Fandom" Point System:</strong>
        table.points-table
            thead
                tr
                    th Action
                    th Weight
                    th Intent Signal
            tbody
                tr
                    td Follow Artist
                    td.points-highlight 5 Points
                    td High Intent (Long-term connection)
                tr
                    td Save / Like Track
                    td.points-highlight 2 Points
                    td Medium Intent (Validation)
                tr
                    td Comment / Share
                    td.points-highlight 1 Point
                    td Active Participation
        p(style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #888; margin-top: 15px;") * passive streams alone do not guarantee allocation. This protects the ecosystem from fraud.

      //- 3. ANTI-FRAUD
      .legal-section
        h2 
          i.fas.fa-shield-alt
          | 3. Anti-Fraud & Engagement Farming
        p Because Auto-Allocation relies on engagement metrics, we strictly prohibit "Engagement Farming."
        p <strong>Prohibited conduct includes:</strong>
        ul
          li Using bots or scripts to artificially generate Follows, Likes, or Comments.
          li Creating "sock puppet" accounts to manipulate the Auto-Allocation pool.
          li Coercing users to allocate funds against their will.
        p Any attempt to manipulate these systems results in immediate account termination and forfeiture of all earnings.

      //- 4. ARTIST CONDUCT
      .legal-section
        h2 
          i.fas.fa-heart
          | 4. Code of Conduct
        p Eporia is a destination for professional-grade audio.
        ul
          li <strong>Quality First:</strong> Upload only your best, finished material.
          li <strong>Respect the Listener:</strong> Do not upload misleading content or "clickbait" audio.
          li <strong>Do No Harm:</strong> Do not use the platform to harass, bully, or incite violence.

      //- 5. TERMINATION
      .legal-section
        h2 
          i.fas.fa-sign-out-alt
          | 5. Freedom to Leave
        p This agreement remains in effect until terminated by either party.
        p You may remove your content at any time. Upon removal, any outstanding wallet balance will be paid out in the next cycle (Net-30).

      //- 6. TAXES
      .legal-section
        h2 
          i.fas.fa-file-invoice-dollar
          | 6. Tax Responsibility
        p You are an independent contractor. You are solely responsible for all taxes on your earnings.
        p Eporia (via Stripe) will issue a <strong>Form 1099-NEC</strong> if your annual earnings exceed the IRS reporting threshold.

      div(style="text-align: center; margin-top: 40px;")
        p(style="opacity: 0.7; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 20px") By clicking "Continue" during setup, you agreed to these terms.
        a(href="/artist/onboarding" style="color: var(--primary); font-weight: 700;") ← Back to Setup